    private function drains(): array
    {
        return [
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Drain Service Overview', 'body' => "A slow drain or backed-up sewer line is more than an inconvenience — it can damage your home and create serious health hazards. Our drain specialists use professional-grade equipment to identify the root cause and clear it completely, not just punch a temporary hole through the clog.\n\nWe start with a camera inspection when needed, so you see exactly what is causing the problem. Then we use the right tool for the job, from motorized drain snakes to high-pressure hydro jetting that scrubs your pipes clean. We leave your home as clean as we found it."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Why Drain Maintenance Matters', 'body' => "Regular drain maintenance is crucial to keep your plumbing flowing freely and avoid costly emergencies. A little upkeep protects your home and your wallet.\n\nPrevent Costly Backups — Routine cleaning clears buildup before it becomes a full blockage, avoiding messy, expensive sewage backups inside your home.\n\nProtect Your Pipes — Grease, hair, and mineral scale slowly corrode and clog your lines. Regular maintenance keeps pipes flowing freely and extends their lifespan.\n\nStop Odors & Health Hazards — Standing water and trapped debris breed bacteria and foul smells. Keeping drains clear protects your home and your family from health risks."],
            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air drain technician clearing a clogged drain in a New Jersey home', 'image_path' => '/img/drains-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Signs Of A Drain Problem', 'body' => "Catching a drain issue early saves you from a messy backup. Watch for these warning signs.\n\nSlow Drainage — Water that pools and takes its time emptying out of a sink, tub, or shower is the earliest sign of a developing clog.\n\nGurgling Sounds — Bubbling or gurgling noises from your drains mean air is trapped behind a blockage struggling to push through the line.\n\nFoul Odors — Persistent sewage or rotten smells usually point to trapped debris, a venting issue, or a partial blockage deep in the line.\n\nFrequent Clogs — If you are plunging the same drain over and over, the real problem is likely further down the line and needs professional clearing.\n\nNoticing one of these warning signs? Schedule a drain inspection and we'll clear it before it becomes an emergency."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Drain Services We Offer', 'body' => "Here's a quick guide to the drain services our licensed technicians provide.\n\nDrain Cleaning — Motorized snaking and augering that breaks up and removes clogs in sinks, tubs, showers, and floor drains quickly.\n\nHydro Jetting — High-pressure water scours the inside of your pipes, blasting away grease, scale, and roots for a like-new, fully clear line.\n\nCamera Inspections — A waterproof camera travels through your line so you see the exact cause and location of the problem before any work begins.\n\nSewer Line Repair — From spot repairs to full line replacement, we fix cracked, collapsed, and root-invaded sewer lines that cause repeat backups.\n\nEmergency Service — When a main line backs up or a drain floods, our team responds the same day to clear the blockage and protect your home."],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How often should I have my drains cleaned?', 'body' => 'For most homes, a professional drain cleaning every one to two years keeps lines clear and prevents backups. Homes with older pipes, large families, or a history of clogs may benefit from yearly service.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What causes a clogged drain?', 'body' => 'The usual culprits are grease and food in kitchen drains, hair and soap scum in bathrooms, mineral buildup, foreign objects, and tree roots invading the main sewer line.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Are chemical drain cleaners safe to use?', 'body' => 'We generally advise against them. Store-bought chemicals can corrode your pipes, are harmful to handle, and often only punch a small hole through the clog instead of clearing it completely.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What is hydro jetting and do I need it?', 'body' => 'Hydro jetting uses high-pressure water to scrub the inside of your pipes clean, removing grease, scale, and roots. It is ideal for stubborn or recurring clogs and badly built-up lines.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How do I know if the clog is in my main sewer line?', 'body' => 'Warning signs include multiple drains backing up at once, gurgling toilets when you run a sink, water pooling around floor drains, or sewage odors. These point to a main line blockage that needs professional clearing.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Can tree roots really damage my sewer line?', 'body' => 'Yes. Roots seek out moisture and can grow into tiny cracks or joints in your sewer line, eventually causing major blockages or breaks. A camera inspection confirms root intrusion so we can clear and repair it.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why does my drain smell bad even after cleaning?', 'body' => 'Lingering odors are often caused by trapped debris, a dry P-trap, or a venting problem rather than a clog. We can diagnose the source and eliminate the smell at its origin.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you use a camera to inspect drains?', 'body' => 'When needed, yes. A drain camera lets us see the exact cause and location of a problem inside your pipes, so we recommend the right fix instead of guessing.'],
